    "extras": [
      "VIVI is the easiest rail backbone for Riga, Jūrmala, Sigulda, and Cēsis; buy tickets in the app or at stations, and validate your train choice carefully because some departures are slightly faster than others.",
      "If you visit Jūrmala by train, you avoid the €450 car-entry fee entirely; that fee only applies to motor vehicles entering the resort zone.",
      "Latvia is very card-friendly, but small cafes and market stalls still sometimes prefer cash for tiny purchases, so keep a little EUR on hand.",
      "Summer daylight is long and comfortable, but Baltic weather shifts quickly: pack a light waterproof even in July if you plan beach time or Gauja hikes.",
      "Book Liepāja buses and central Riga stays ahead for midsummer weekends because coastal demand spikes faster than prices elsewhere in the country."
    ],
